                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.00/911a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-01T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 1, 1942—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1008. Will you please see Casey at as early a moment as possible and referring to
                    the situation reported in Beirut’s no. 319 of September 1, 1 p.m. ask that he
                    give you for the information of your Government as full an indication of his
                    views in this connection as possible. Needless to add the policy of the American
                    Government is directed towards preventing this threatened break in
                    Franco-British relations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
